headline: Will Record Recurring Revenue and Upgraded Guidance Reshape Trimble's (TRMB) Long-Term Story?
summary: Trimble recently reported stronger-than-expected third-quarter results, highlighted by record gross margins, annualized recurring revenue of US$2.3 billion, and raised full-year 2025 financial guidance driven by successful execution of its Connect & Scale strategy. Alongside its positive earnings, Trimble announced a series of software enhancements and integrations, such as advanced features in WorksManager and ProjectSight 360 Capture, demonstrating its efforts to expand interoperability...
